<title>HONG KONG: Aeon Credit year net rises 61.83 pct.</title>
<headline>Aeon Credit year net rises 61.83 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended February 20</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   21.99  vs 16.46</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    5.5    vs 5.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  nil    vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    76.89  vs 47.51</p>
<p>    Turnover		     347.10 vs 238.51</p>
<p>    Company name		 Aeon Credit Service (Asia) Co Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  June 4-11</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   July 14</p>
<p>NOTE - Aeon Credit Service, a unit of Aeon Credit Service Co 8570.Q of Japan, is a consumer credit services provider and credit card issuer.</p>
<p>Total dividend for year is eight H.K. cents (including interim dividend of 2.5 cents) vs five cents.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
